    "), limiting access to data at all stages , and discarding both collected and processed data as soon as possible .",
    "That is, data minimization implies restricting access to all data to the smallest set of people possible, often accomplished via security mechanisms, such as encryption at rest and on the wire, access-control lists, and more nascent technologies such as secure multiparty computation and trusted execution environments, to be discussed later.",
    "These processes are perhaps best embodied via federated learning and analytics (Kairouz, McMahan, Avent, et al., 2021; McMahan et al., 2017).",
